the european community 
the basic mistake is the belief that stable and adequate 
incomes for farmers can be achieved through agricultural price 
support the study said 
as historical experience has vividly demonstrated this 
instrument is neither effective nor efficient 
it added that the system has brought windfall gains to efficient 
largescale european farmers and has not given adequate income to 
small ones 
the study the common agricultural policy of the european 
community was written by six experts of the fund which is owned 
by 151 governments 
european farmers get protection from foreign competition by a 
system of variable levies on imports these are customs duties that 
rise and fall with world prices payable by european importers so 
that domestic products are cheaper to european consumers at any 
given moment farmers also benefit from price supports to keep their 
incomes relatively high this system helped western europe become 
selfsufficient in food after world war ii but in recent years it 
has encouraged the creation of huge product surpluses 
the community has a problem in exporting its surpluses and uses 
european tax money to subsidize the sales and to pay the enormous 
cost of storing the excess 
the us government also uses price supports to keep farmers 
incomes high restricts imports and thus creates surpluses it also 
uses tax money to subsidize exports but according to the funds 
