security for soviet leader mikhail gorbachevs 
visit will be extremely tight with 6600 police officers working 
overtime in part because of the citys history of antisoviet 
incidents 
security will be probably as comprehensive and as important as 
any visit we have had in years and years gillian martin sorensen 
the citys liaison to the united nations said monday 
gorbachev was to arrive in the city today on wednesday he is 
scheduled to address the general assembly and have lunch with 
president reagan and presidentelect george bush 
among gorbachevs expected sightseeing stops on thursday are the 
javits convention center the metropolitan museum of art and central 
park he departs for cuba on friday 
