<DOCNO> AP881206-0142 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
united nations the soviet union which once scorned the united 
nations has embraced the world body under president mikhail s 
gorbachev as a prized foreign policy tool to promote his new 
political thinking and help extricate moscow from regional 
conflicts 
now the soviet union has become the mover and shaker the 
biggest booster of an international forum it once despised as 
ineffectual or westernbiased now more than ever the soviet union 
appears to be a team player the united states appears selfisolated 
gorbachev who plans to make his first address to the 159nation 
world body on wednesday is expected to deliver a dazzling tour de 
force on visionary foreign policy he is expected to cover issues 
ranging from the environment to conventional disarmament to the 
middle east and the need to promote the united nations as a 
oncediscarded multilateral forum whose time has come 
for several years the soviet union has been carrying out a 
public relations offensive at the united nations and has launched 
initiatives here as part of an international pattern of new soviet 
ideas on peacemaking on almost every continent 
gorbachevs visit comes at a time when the us relations with 
the world body strained during the entire reagan administration 
have soured abruptly over the us refusal to grant palestine 
liberation organization chairman yasser arafat a visa to speak here 
last week 
the united states also is more than half a billion dollars in 
arrears in its un budget and peacekeeping dues 
by contrast the soviet union has been repaying its back dues and 
now owes 159 million in regular budget and peacekeeping dues 
the soviet union has discovered the united nations which it 
either had ignored or had exploited as a polarized forum where it 
joined the third world in scoring points against the united states 
but today the eastwest climate had warmed dramatically and the 
soviet union is participating as never before in the united nations 
it is calling for the world body to play a larger role in 
peacekeeping resolving international conflicts in verification of 
disarmament and in fields from outer space to narcotics trafficking 
it has become among the least ideological least contentious 
members known more today for listening than for rhetoric 
the soviet union has viewed the unmediated agreement on 
afghanistan as a facesaving way to end its involvement in a costly 
conflict and withdraw its troops likewise the soviet union has 
encouraged un peacemaking efforts in cambodia where moscow has 
backed the vietnamese occupation it also sees a un plan for 
southern africa as a means to end the involvement of sovietbacked 
cuban troops in angola 
this year for the first time the united states and soviet union 
voted together on the afghanistan question expressing satisfaction 
with un efforts and soviet troop withdrawal 
while the united states tends to resolve its problems without the 
united nations the soviet union now tends to work within the un 
system 
now it is the soviet union more often than the united states 
which votes with the majority and is known for compromise seeking 
consensus floating ideas then going back to the drawing board and 
revising them for the soviet union all ideas appear to be open for 
discussion 
the soviet union now emphasizes its new thinking and a shift 
away from the old eastwest adversarial relationship it now talks 
of multipolarity an interdependent world security which depends on 
confidence not arms and disarmament to a level of 
selfsufficiency at which no one can successfully launch 
aggression 
the soviet union has been pushing for broader un peacekeeping 
powers including a un naval force in the persian gulf which would 
eliminate the need for a us naval presence in the iraniraq war 
it has called for meetings of the 15member security council at 
the foreign ministers level to discuss trouble spots around the 
world for several years it has been promoting a new comprehensive 
system of international security a vague concept covering 
everything from humanitarian issues to greater openness on military 
spending 
the united states opposes the concept as being undefined 
encroaching on national prerogatives and possibly giving the united 
nations too great a role 
last september soviet foreign minister eduard a shevardnadze 
delivered an extraordinary even revolutionary un speech in which 
he said class struggle played no part in soviet foreign policy he 
devoted more discussion to the environment than to disarmament and 
