<TEXT>
a report released a us human rights group 
tuesday criticized israel for imprisoning palestinians without trial 
and inhumane conditions at a prison camp in the negev desert 
the lawyers committee for human rights based in new york city 
compiled its 95page report after factfinding missions to israel 
and the occupied territories its representatives heard testimony 
from palestinian lawyers and human rights workers and interviewed 
israeli officials 
among cases cited in the report is the detention in recent months 
of four palestinian field workers for al haq a human rights group 
in the occupied west bank and two lawyers from the occupied gaza 
strip 
all four were placed under administrative detention an emergency 
measure allowing for detention of up to six months without charges 
or trial the two lawyers have been released 
the administrative detention is a serious blow to 
independent human rights monitoring in the west bank the report 
said 
it also outlined abuses in the ketziot prison where thousands of 
palestinians have been detained during the yearold palestinian 
revolt against israeli rule in the occupied territories 
about 2500 palestinians are believed held in ketziot 1500 
under administrative detention 
ketziots location in a remote part of israel proper its 
extremely harsh desert climate and its crowded inhumane living 
conditions combine to create an untenable environment in which to 
maintain longterm detainees the report said 
at ketziot arabs are routinely forced to stand in the sweltering 
desert heat for hours water supplies are inadequate and prisoners 
are sometimes beaten it said 
ketziot inmates made similar complaints when an associated press 
reporter visited the prison in june 
detention in israel of residents of the occupied territories 
violates the fourth geneva convention which states that detainees 
in an occupied country may not be moved to another country the 
report contended 
it quotes lt gen dan shomron the army chief of staff as 
saying ketziots location may be a contradiction of the geneva 
convention but israel has the right to transfer prisoners into a 
sovereign part of the country 
shomron also is quoted as saying the army is trying to improve 
conditions at the prison but its not a hotel 
the lawyers committee for human rights was established in 1978 
and has investigated human rights abuses in more than 25 countries 
this report was written by the executive director michael posner 
and virginia sherry 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

