rebuilt the city gave the rebuilt homes to all the residents except 
ms james 
her suit against the city to recover the house which is under 
24hour police guard is pending in common pleas court 
while neighbors dont want ms james to get the house back they 
dont want it sold until the city can come to an agreement with her 
said one resident gerald renfrow 
shes not going to walk away with no money and no house and 
thats going to keep us in the middle of their fight he said 
sixtyone houses were destroyed after police dropped a bomb on 
the roof of the fortified move row house in an effort to evict the 
members john africa ms james son frank james africa and nine 
others in the house died in the siege 
